verbose_text: Although the effects of either calcitriol or CaSR on osteoclasts activities are controversial in previous publications XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR - XREF_BIBR, in this study, our results showed that the calcitriol loaded scaffolds could increase the expression of CaSR but decrease the c-fos and NFATc1 expression (the marker of osteoclastogenesis) of bone marrow monocytes (BMMs), under the stimulation of 50ng/mL of RANKL.
